---
description: No UI change during production fixes
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

For production fixes, release fixes, QA fixes, button wiring, route creation, and navigation fixes:

Strictly forbidden:
- changing UI
- changing layout
- changing spacing
- changing styling
- changing structure of rendered visible content
- replacing components for aesthetic reasons
- changing copy/text unless required to fix a bug
- changing iconography
- changing visual hierarchy

Allowed:
- local code fixes
- navigation fixes
- event handler fixes
- route creation
- crash fixes
- import fixes
- guard clauses
- defensive programming
- async reliability fixes

If a fix would require a visible UI change:
- stop first
- explain why
- do not proceed without explicit permission

Default behavior:
all production fixes must be invisible to the user visually.
